¹ Duplicarzos.] These were soldiers who were rewarded for some services with a double allowance of bread. It was usual with the Romans and Spartans to reward valour in this way. See B. 7. c. 37.-B. 24. c. 47.—Herod. B. 6. 57. The Spartan king had always a double portion of food at the public feast, that he might be able to reward any person he pleased for his merit.
